pull.title: developer-notes: add reference to snake_case and PascalCase
pull.body:
CamelCase is ambiguous as it refers to both lowerCamelCase and
UpperCamelCase, whereas PascalCase is only UpperCamelCase.

events.body: I realize that the way `CamelCase` was written, it implied UpperCamelCase, but I still did a double take as I have only ever seen camelCase refer to lowerCamelCase.

> Variable and namespace names are all lowercase, and may use _ to separate words.

This describes what is called "snake_case". Maybe the documentation should mention that too.
Interesting; I had never heard of PascalCase, and only seen CamelCase to refer to it.
That is interesting ;) I made another revision: `UpperCamelCase (PascalCase)`.
Please rename PR title and commit to something like `Add reference to snake_case and PascalCase in developer notes`. Missing snake_case in PR description. Otherwise ACK.

events.message:
developer-notes: add reference to snake_case and PascalCase

CamelCase is ambiguous as it refers to both lowerCamelCase and
UpperCamelCase, whereas PascalCase is only UpperCamelCase.
